The  stocks, which include major tech firms Alphabet,  Microsoft Tesla Meta Platforms Amazon.com Apple  and  Nvidia  comprise around a third of the  total market value.  Nearly a third of the estimated $536.3 billion in collective profit from S&P 500 companies in the second quarter will come from just two sectors: information technology and communications services.
